    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n1069" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀντι-κρύ̄, ἀντικρύς</span></b> :
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">opposite, straightforward, straight through;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἀντικρὺ μάχεσθαι</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 5.130</span></i>, 819; w. gen., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ὀιστὸν ἴαλλεν</span> | <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">Ἕκτορος
            ἀντικρύ̄,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 8.301</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            ἀποφάναι</span>, ‘outright,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            7.362</span></i>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">; ἀντικρὺ̄ δ᾽ ἀπάραξε</span>, ‘completely’
          off, <i><span class="en">Il. 16.116</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.866</span></i>; often joined w. foll. prep.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">παραί, διά, κατά, ἀνά</span>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
